thread.title: Vancouver police seek tips in locating runaway boy, 12
thread.title_full: Vancouver police seek tips in locating runaway boy, 12 | OregonLive.com

author: Nuran Alteir | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Vancouver police seek tips in locating runaway boy, 12
text:
Justin Chan, 12, ran away from home on Oct. 20, 2015. Vancouver Police Department Police are asking the public for help in finding a 12-year-old boy who ran away from his Vancouver home Tuesday.
Justin Chan, 12, has not been seen or heard from since Tuesday morning, Vancouver officer Ilia Botvinnik wrote in a news release. Justin attends a local middle school in Vancouver and lives in the area of Northeast Fourth Plain Boulevard and Northeast 57th Avenue.
"Justin was last seen wearing a long sleeved red shirt, tan pants, black shoes, and a black backpack," Botvinnik said.
Anyone who sees Justin is asked to call Vancouver Police Department's dispatch center at 360-696-4461.
